Chocolate covered strawberries tip 

When you dip strawberries always leave the bottom somehow uncovered. If you cover your berry entirely like the strawberry on your right, game over ! 
Why? 
Well, strawberries need to “BREATH” strawberries will produce tiny amounts of ethylene and this gas needs to be released ! If you cover your strawberry all this gas will have no way to exit ! And by the time your customer wants to enjoy their berries they most likely have a mushy strawberry and who wants that eeeeew! Let them girls LEAK !

The only times we recommend you covering your entire strawberries is if you’re creating towers, and other arrangements that you know for sure will be devoured in hours ! 

If you dio your berries overnight please use this method ! 
Strawberries ARE SUPPOSED TO LEAK !
